# Meta Ads + Catalog Automation Plan (Dealer System)

## Objective
Build a fully automated system that:
- Ingests dealer inventory from your website
- Syncs it to a centralized Meta catalog
- Segments inventory by dealer
- Prepares ads in a paused state
- Waits 7 days for validation and funding
- Automatically launches ads if conditions are met
- Prevents overspending using strict guardrails

---

## System Architecture

### Source of Truth
- Website: forestryequipmentsales.com
- All listings originate here
- Listings must be clean, published, and accessible

### Meta Assets (Centralized)
- One Meta Business Manager
- One Ad Account
- One Master Catalog
- One Pixel
- Product Sets (one per dealer)

### Automation Layers
- Playwright → setup, login, verification
- Meta Marketing API → catalog sync, ads, budgets, automation

---

## Budget Model

### Pro Dealer Plan Example
- Pro Dealer pays: $1,000/month
- Ad Spend Allocation: 30% = $300/month

### Daily Budget
$300 / 30 = $10/day

### Budget Guardrails
- Daily budget set at ad set level
- Optional lifetime budget cap
- Auto-pause rules if spend exceeds limits
- No campaign launches without funding verification

---

## Step 1: Meta Setup (Playwright)

### Goal
Automate initial setup and extract required IDs

### Tasks
- Login to Meta Business Manager
- Create or verify:
  - Ad Account
  - Catalog
  - Pixel
- Navigate to:
  - Ads Manager
  - Commerce Manager

### Extract and Store:
- ad_account_id (act_XXXX)
- catalog_id
- pixel_id
- page_id

### Output
Store all IDs in your database per environment

---

## Step 2: Dealer Onboarding Flow

### Trigger
Dealer signs up on your website

### Flow
1. Assign unique `dealer_id`
2. Dealer uploads inventory
3. Listings are published and live

### Required Listing Fields
- id
- title
- description
- price
- image_url
- condition
- availability
- location (city, state)
- url (canonical listing URL)
- dealer_id

---

## Step 3: Catalog Feed Automation

### Feed URL
https://www.forestryequipmentsales.com/feed/meta-catalog.xml

### Feed Requirements
Each item must include:
- id
- title
- description
- availability
- condition
- price
- link
- image_link
- brand (manufacturer)
- custom_label_0 = dealer_id
- seller name

### Sync Frequency
- Daily

### API Endpoint
POST /{catalog_id}/items_batch

### Behavior
- Add new listings
- Update existing listings
- Remove sold listings

---

## Step 4: Product Set Creation (Per Dealer / Pro Dealer)

### Logic
Each dealer gets a product set

### Filter Rule
custom_label_0 = dealer_id

### Example
Dealer A → Product Set A  
Dealer B → Product Set B

### Automation
- Create via API when dealer signs up
- Store product_set_id

---

## Step 5: Campaign Creation (Paused)

### Trigger
Dealer has:
- Inventory uploaded
- Product set created

### Campaign Setup

#### Campaign
- Objective: Sales
- Type: Catalog Sales
- Status: PAUSED

#### Ad Set
- Product Set: dealer-specific
- Budget: $10/day (based on 30%) for pro dealer, and 30% of subscription cost for dealer too
- Optimization: Conversions
- Pixel: assigned
- Status: PAUSED

#### Targeting
- Location:
  - Option A: United States
  - Option B: Radius 250 miles from dealer
- Age: 35–65+
- Gender: Men
- Interests (max 3–5):
  - Forestry
  - Logging
  - Heavy Equipment

#### Ad
- Format: Dynamic Catalog Ad
- Creative pulled from feed
- Status: PAUSED

---

## Step 6: 3-Day Delay System

### Purpose
Ensure:
- Inventory is valid
- Feed is syncing correctly
- Account is funded
- No broken listings

### Logic
Wait 7 days after:
- First listing is published

### Store:
launch_date = created_at + 3 days

---

## Step 7: Funding Verification

### Before Launch
Check:
- Payment method exists OR
- Available funds > threshold

### If NOT funded:
- Do NOT launch ads
- Retry daily

---

## Step 8: Launch Automation

### Conditions Required
- Current date >= launch_date
- Inventory count > minimum threshold
- Catalog sync successful
- Account funded

### Action
- Activate campaign
- Activate ad sets
- Activate ads

---

## Step 9: Overspend Protection

### Rules
- Daily budget enforced at ad set level
- Optional lifetime budget cap
- Monitor spend via API

### Auto Pause Conditions
- Spend > 110% of monthly budget
- No inventory remaining
- Feed errors detected

### Monitoring Frequency
- Every 6–12 hours

---

## Step 10: Playwright Responsibilities

### Use Playwright for:
- Logging into Meta
- Creating initial assets
- Verifying:
  - Catalog exists
  - Product sets exist
  - Campaign exists
- Extracting IDs
- Screenshot logging (QA)

### DO NOT use Playwright for:
- Daily ad management
- Budget control
- Campaign automation

---

## Step 11: API Responsibilities

### Use Meta Marketing API for:
- Catalog sync
- Product set creation
- Campaign creation
- Budget updates
- Ad activation/pause
- Spend monitoring

---

## Step 12: Automation Flow Summary

1. Dealer signs up
2. Inventory uploaded
3. Feed syncs to catalog
4. Product set created
5. Campaign created (paused)
6. Wait 7 days
7. Check funding
8. Launch ads
9. Monitor + enforce budget rules

---

## Key Principles

- One master catalog (never per dealer)
- Dealer segmentation via product sets
- API handles all ongoing logic
- Playwright only sets up and verifies
- Never launch ads immediately
- Always enforce budget caps

---

## Final Outcome

- Fully automated dealer onboarding
- Inventory → catalog → ads pipeline
- Controlled ad spend (30% rule)
- Zero manual ad setup after system is built
- Scalable to unlimited dealers